8 "§ 88B-4. Powers and duties of the Board.
9 (a) The Board shall have the following powers and duties:
10 (1) To administer and interpret this Chapter.
11 (2) To adopt, amend, and repeal rules to carry out the provisions of this Chapter.
12 (3) To examine and determine the qualifications and fitness of applicants for
13 licensure under this Chapter.
14 (4) To issue, renew, deny, restrict, suspend, or revoke licenses.
15 (5) To conduct investigations of alleged violations of this Chapter or the Board's
16 rules.
17 (6) To collect fees required by G.S. 88B-20 and any other monies permitted by
18 law to be paid to the Board.
19 (7) To approve new cosmetic art schools.
20 (7a) To adopt rules for cosmetic art schools.
21 (8) To inspect cosmetic art schools and shops.schools, cosmetic art shops, and
22 mobile cosmetic art shops.
23 (9) To adopt rules for the sanitary management and physical requirements of
24 cosmetic art shops shops, mobile cosmetic art shops, and cosmetic art schools.
25 (10) To establish a curriculum for each course of study required for the issuance of
26 a license or certification issued under this Chapter.
27 (11) To employ an executive director and any additional professional, clerical, or
28 special personnel necessary to carry out the provisions of this Chapter, and to
29 purchase or rent necessary office space, equipment, and supplies.
30 (12) To adopt a seal.
31 (13) To carry out any other actions authorized by this Chapter.
32 (b) A member of the Board shall have the authority to inspect cosmetic art shops shops,
33 mobile cosmetic art shops, and cosmetic art schools at any reasonable hour to determine
34 compliance with the provisions of this Chapter if the inspection is made: (i) at the request of the
35 Board, or with the approval of the chair or the executive director as the result of a complaint
36 made to the Board or a problem reported by an inspector, or (ii) at the request of an inspector
37 who deems it necessary to request the assistance of a Board member and who has the prior
38 approval of the chair or executive director to do so. A Board member who makes an inspection
39 pursuant to this subsection shall file a report with the Board before requesting reimbursement for
40 expenses.
41 (c) The Board shall keep a record of its proceedings relating to the issuance, renewal,
42 denial, restriction, suspension, and revocation of licenses. licenses and certifications. This record
43 shall also contain each licensee's name, business and home addresses, license number, and the
44 date the license was issued.
45 (d) The Board shall offer or approve a 10-hour course in infection control for natural hair
46 care specialists. The Board shall make available at least one qualifying course on its website, free
47 of charge.
48 "§ 88B-5. Meetings and compensation of the Board.
49 (a) Each member of the Board shall receive compensation for services and expenses as
50 provided in G.S. 93B-5, but shall be limited to payment for services deemed official business of
51 the Board when such business exceeds three continuous hours per day. Official business of the
