1 Board includes meetings called by the chair and time spent inspecting cosmetic art shops and
2 shops, mobile cosmetic art shops, and cosmetic art schools as permitted by this Chapter. No
3 payment for per diem or travel expenses shall be authorized or paid for Board meetings other
4 than those called by the chair. The Board may annually select one member to attend a national
5 state board of cosmetic arts meeting on official business of the Board. No other Board members
6 shall be authorized to attend trade shows or to travel out-of-state at the Board's expense.
7 (b) The Board shall hold four regular meetings a year in the months of January, April,
8 July, and October. The chair may call additional meetings whenever necessary.
9 "§ 88B-6. Board office, employees, funds, budget requirements.
10 (a) The Board shall maintain its office in Wake County, North Carolina.
11 (b) The Board shall employ an executive director who shall not be a member of the Board.
12 The executive director shall keep all records of the Board, issue all necessary notices, and
13 perform any other duties required by the Board.
14 (c) With the approval of the Director of the Budget and the Office of State Human
15 Resources, the Board may employ as many inspectors, investigators, and other staff as necessary
16 to perform inspections and other duties prescribed by the Board. Inspectors and investigators
17 shall be experienced in all parts of cosmetic art and shall have authority to examine cosmetic art
18 shops shops, mobile cosmetic art shops, and cosmetic art schools during business hours to
19 determine compliance with this Chapter.
20 "§ 88B-7. Qualifications for licensing cosmetologists.
21 The Board shall issue a license to practice as a cosmetologist to any individual who meets all
22 of the following requirements:
23 (1) Successful completion of at least 1,500 1,200 hours of a cosmetology
24 curriculum in an approved cosmetic art school, or at least 1,200 hours of a
25 cosmetology curriculum in an approved cosmetic art school and completion
26 of an apprenticeship for a period of at least six months under the direct
27 supervision of a cosmetologist, as certified by sworn affidavit of three licensed
28 cosmetologists or by other evidence satisfactory to the Board.school.
29 (2) Passage of an examination conducted by the Board.
30 (3) Payment of the fees required by G.S. 88B-20.
31 "§ 88B-8. Qualifications for licensing apprentices.
32 The Board shall issue a license to practice as an apprentice to any individual who meets all
33 of the following requirements:
34 (1) Successful completion of at least 1,200 hours of a cosmetology curriculum in
35 an approved cosmetic art school.
36 (2) Passage of an examination conducted by the Board.
37 (3) Payment of the fees required by G.S. 88B-20.
38 "§ 88B-8.1. Qualifications for licensing as a hair designer.
39 The Board shall issue a license to practice as a hair designer to any individual who meets all
40 of the following requirements:
41 (1) Successful completion of at least 900 hours of a hair design curriculum in an
42 approved cosmetic art school.
43 (2) Passage of an examination conducted by the Board.
44 (3) Payment of the fees required by G.S. 88B-20.
45 "§ 88B-9. Qualifications for licensing as an esthetician.
46 The Board shall issue a license to practice as an esthetician to any individual who meets all
47 of the following requirements:
48 (1) Successful completion of at least 600 hours of an esthetics curriculum in an
49 approved cosmetic art school.school, or, for a licensed hair designer,
50 successful completion of at least 300 hours of an esthetics curriculum in an
51 approved cosmetic art school.
