General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (4) Permitting any individual to practice cosmetic art without a license license,
2 infection control certification, or temporary employment permit, with an
3 expired license or temporary employment permit, or with an invalid license
4 license, infection control certification, or temporary employment permit.
5 (5) Obtaining or attempting to obtain a license for money or other thing of value
6 other than the required fee or by fraudulent misrepresentation.
7 (6) Practicing or attempting to practice by fraudulent misrepresentation.
8 (7) Willful failure to display a certificate of license or an infection control
9 certification as required by G.S. 88B-23.
10 (8) Willful violation of the rules adopted by the Board.
