14 "§ 88B-25. Exemptions.
15 The following persons are exempt from the provisions of this Chapter while engaged in the
16 proper discharge of their professional duties:
17 (1) Undertakers and funeral establishments licensed under G.S. 90-210.25.
18 (2) Persons authorized to practice medicine or surgery under Chapter 90 of the
19 General Statutes.
20 (3) Nurses licensed under Chapter 90 of the General Statutes.
21 (4) Commissioned medical or surgical officers of the United States Army, Air
22 Force, Navy, Marine Corps, Space Force, or Coast Guard.
23 (5) A person employed in a cosmetic art shop or mobile cosmetic art shop whose
24 duties are expressly confined to the shampooing or blow drying of hair,
25 provided that the person shall comply with rules adopted by the Board relating
26 to sanitary management of cosmetic art shops.shops and mobile cosmetic art
27 shops.
28 "§ 88B-26. Rules to be posted.
29 (a) The Board shall furnish a copy of its rules relating to sanitary management of
30 cosmetic art shops shops, mobile cosmetic art shops, and cosmetic art schools to each shop shop,
31 mobile cosmetic art shop, and school licensed by the Board. Each shop shop, mobile cosmetic
32 art shop, and school shall post the rules in a conspicuous place.
33 (b) The Board shall furnish a copy of its rules relating to curriculum and schools to each
34 licensed cosmetic art school. Each cosmetic art school shall make these rules available to all
35 teachers and students.
36 "§ 88B-27. Inspections.
37 Any inspector or other authorized representative of the Board may enter any cosmetic art
38 shop or shop, mobile cosmetic art shop, or cosmetic art school to inspect it for compliance with
39 this Chapter and the Board's rules. All persons practicing cosmetic art in a shop shop, mobile
40 cosmetic art shop, or school shall, upon request, present satisfactory proof of identification.
41 Satisfactory proof shall be in the form of a photographic driver's license or photographic
42 identification card issued by any state, federal, or other government entity. The Board may
43 require a cosmetic art shop or shop, mobile cosmetic art shop, or cosmetic art school to be
44 inspected as a condition for license renewal.
45 …."
